Title: Long Z2 Bike with LT Intervals: 3 X 10 (or 5 miles) min TT... can switch yesterday and today
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Ride 20 minutes in Aerobic Zone 2, then do 4 X 30 second pickups with 1 minute recovery between each. Ride a few minutes easy, stop and stretch if feeling tight. Bike 3 x 10 minutes HARD building from high Zone 3 to low Zone 4. Ride 5-8 minute recoveries between intervals. Ride any remaining time in low to mid zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Title: Z2 Run, MAF Test
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test: how fast you run without going anaerobic at all. This test can be done on the track or the treadmill. (Track is preferable). Warmup with 15 minutes easy running. TEST: Run 3 miles continuous in the last few beats of your Aerobic Heart Rate Zone 2. Do not go over zone 2! Cool down with 5-10 minutes of easy running. Record the Total Time for three miles as well as mile splits. If done on the treadmill, get total time and average speed, if possible. Run on a 1% incline for MAF Test if done on the treadmill.
AthleteComments: *01/03/2019 Keith Kruelskie: Hard to keep a constant HR on a treadmill in hot and humid gym...*

Title: Swim, Tempo 600 ladders {3000}
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 500 freestyle. Swim 2 x 100 done as 50 high elbow drill/50 swim Swim three sets of: 200 HARD, race pace 2 x 100 easy 4 x 50, HARD, race pace [take 10 sec rest in-between each and 1 minute between the three ] Kick 2 x 50 with kickboard. Swim 6 x 50 with buoy (10 sec RI) Cool down 100 easy.

Title: Z2 Ride with 2 x 5 min On/Offs 6/24 sprint/rest
WorkoutDescription: Warmup: Ride in Zone 1 to 2 for 15 minutes Keep your cadence over 85 rpm Perform 2 x 5 minute On/Off intervals. Start the interval with a 6 second sprint at 95%, recover for 24 seconds with easy spinning, then sprint again for 6 seconds and recover for 24.... Repeat for the interval duration. Use a fairly big gear. Cool down 5 minutes easy

Title: Run, Tempo Fartlek: 30/60/2min & Form Sprints
WorkoutDescription: Tempo Fartlek (alternating speeds) Run. Warmup 10 minutes easy. Run 4 x 30 seconds at 5K effort with 30 seconds easy jog in-between. Run 2 minutes easy. Run 4 x 60 seconds at 5K effort with 60 seconds easy jog in-between. Run 2 minutes easy. Run 2 x 2 minutes at 5K effort with 2 minutes easy jog in-between. Run 2 minutes easy. Do 4 x ~15 seconds "Form Sprints" where you run as fast as you can with perfect form. Do not run long enough where these really tire you. Get up to your max, run some strides at max speed, then slow it down. Run easy 45 seconds in-between. Run any remaining time/mileage in zone 1/2. Cool down 5 minutes easy.

Title: Z2 Aerobic Run before or after the bike
WorkoutDescription: Warmup and cooldown as needed. Endurance run before or after bike session. All zone 2.

Title: Supplemental Strength C (2 rounds)
WorkoutDescription: Do two sets of 15 repetitions of each exercise, using approximately 60 percent of your one-repetition maximum resistance. Concentrate on maintaining good form and on taking a full two seconds on the concentric movement (lifting the weight) and four seconds on the eccentric movement (lowering the weight). Rest 30 to 60 seconds between sets. Squat Lat pulldown Leg extension Bench Press Leg curl (hamstrings) Biceps curl Triceps exercise (choice) Seated row Abdominals (curl-up, reverse & oblique curl, crunch) Side/lateral shoulder raise

Title: Swim, Z2/Z3 ladder 100s-200-50s {3500}
WorkoutDescription: 400 swim/200 choice/200 pull 3 times through: 4 x 100s descending 1-4 200 easy 4 x 50s FAST 200 easy pull Take 15 sec RI between everything 1 minute between sets 100 cooldown

Title: Long bike with 30 minute Z2 Aerobic Bike MAF Test (to test avg speed and/or power)
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test to test aerobic capacity on the bike. After a 30 minute warmup, ride approximately 30 minute course in the top of Zone 2. Pick a course you can do in the future. It needs to be a loop an out and back to control for climate and course. If using power, this can be done on the trainer. Just put it on ergo mode or pick a course that is flat or gently rolling. For the 30 minutes... Record average HR, max HR, average speed, average non-norm power (if you have it), total time and exact distance. Also record details of the course used and any other necessary details. DO NOT GO OVER Z2 or the test is irrelevant. Ride the rest of the ride in Aerobic Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Title: Long run with Fartlek: Speed Ladder
WorkoutDescription: Tempo Fartlek (alternating speeds) Run. Warmup 10-15 minutes easy. Run most of today's run in Zone 2. After halfway, include two sets of the following ladder: 30 sec fast/30 sec easy 60 sec fast/60 sec easy 90 sec fact/90 sec easy 2 minutes fast *5 minutes easy between sets Fast for this workout is close to your 5K effort/speed, or around 90%. Do not use heartrate for these intervals since they are short in duration. The remainder of the run should be in zones 1-2. Cool down 5 minutes easy.

Title: Z2 Aerobic Bike with 5 x 2 min hard intervals, 5 x 1 max
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy spinning. Then ride for 5 minutes alternating "10 seconds on/10 seconds off." On means hard, off means soft-pedaling. Ride 5 x 2 minutes very hard (threshold to V02max) efforts, preferably on an uphill, big-gear or into a headwind. These should go into your upper HR zones. Take 2 minute recoveries. Then ride 5 by 1 minute all out efforts. Take 90 second recoveries. Ride any remaining time in Z1 easy. Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Title: Long Z2 Aerobic Bike with 8 x 1 Pickups
WorkoutDescription: Warmup up 15 minutes easy. Ride the first half of this ride in high zone 1 to low zone 2 (with the intent of the workout to finish harder than you start). In the second half, include 8 x 1 min HARD (like 90-95% effort). Heartrate should come up into zone 3, but how high depends on your overall fatigue-level today. Just push these by feel and pace it so that you can do all 10 of them at 90-95% effort. Take at least 2 minutes easy in between endurance pace in the Aerobic Endurance Zone 2. Cool down 15 minutes minutes easy. Cadence: 80-105 rpm, with cadence mostly in the upper 80s to 90s. Terrain: Flat to rolling RPE (1-10): 7

Title: ~Long Easy Endurance Run
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 5-10 minutes easy jogging. Run EASY endurance in at no higher than a 6 on the RPE scale of 1-10. Keep your breathing very comfortable. Don't worry about pace!! Cool down 5 minutes easy jogging or walking. Try to include some hills.

Title: Run, MAF Test
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test: how fast you run without going anaerobic at all. This test can be done on the track or the treadmill. (Track is preferable). Warmup with 2 miles easy running. TEST: Run 3 miles continuous in the last few beats of your Aerobic Heart Rate Zone 2. Do not go over zone 2! Cool down with 1 mile easy running. Record the Total Time for three miles as well as mile splits. If done on the treadmill, get total time and average speed, if possible. Run on a 1% incline for MAF Test if done on the treadmill.

Title: Long Trainer Ride with Tempo/Strength/Drills
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15-30 minutes easy. DRILLS: Riding in the aerobic zone 2, include 4 sets of the following (2 min climb at 70 rpm, 2 min flat road, 2 min very fast cadence over 110 rpm at light resistance). The climbs add some strength-work, and the high cadence drills work on your neuro-muscular cycling speed. Ride 10 minutes is zone 2. TEMPO: Then ride 3 x 10 minutes working your way from low to mid zone 3. Do not go into zone 4. Recover 5 minutes in-between. DRILL: Recover with 10 minutes alternating 2 minutes Left leg, 1 minute both legs, 2 minutes right leg. GRADUAL CLIMBS: Then climb 4 x 3 minutes at 70 rpm, seated. Take 3 minutes high-cadence spinning in-between. HR can go into low zone 3, but don't force it. Ride 10 minutes in Zone 2. STEEP CLIMBS: Ride 8 x 30 seconds at max gearing (treat this as a real "strength" session). Recover 90 seconds in-between. These power climbs can be seated or standing. DRILL: Do 4 x 1 minute "Spin-up" where you start with a small gear, spin to your max cadence (110-120?), then add a few gears until you feel your cadence slow just a little. Hold this high rpm for 1 minute. Take 90 seconds recovery in-between. Ride any remaining time in Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes.

Are you stretching? Do you have any sniffles/sore throat/cough/abnormal fatigue, etc? Title: 3/20 Anaerobic/Aerobic LT Test
WorkoutDescription: Warmup: 20 minutes easy in Zones 1 and 2. Ride 3 X 1 minute fast pedaling at 100rpm to get things moving. Ride 5 minutes easy. Perform the test on a relatively flat road or on an indoor trainer. Main Set: Ride 3 minutes ALL OUT BEST EFFORT. Ride easy 10 minutes. Rice 20 min Time Trial BEST EFFORT. Make both of these tests as steady as possible. Do not go too hard at the beginning so that you can't hold a steady effort. Ride any remaining time easy. Cool Down 110 minutes. Record your average heartrate and average normalized power (if using a powermeter) for both the 3 minute and 20 minute efforts.

Title: Bike, Z2 MAF Test
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test to test aerobic capacity on the bike. After a 15-30 minute warmup, ride approximately 8-10 mile course (flat or rolling hills) in the top of Z2. Record average HR, max HR, average speed, total time and exact distance. Also record details of the course used and any other necessary details. Can be done on the Computrainer. Pick a route you can do again in the future. Ride the rest of the ride in Aerobic Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy. Don't force this test. If heartrate isn't getting up to the top of zone 2, then you can do the test on a day you feel better.

Title: Run, MAF Test
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test: how fast you run without going anaerobic at all. This test can be done on the track or the treadmill. (Track is preferable). Warmup with 2 miles easy running. TEST: Run 3 miles continuous in the last few beats of your Aerobic Heart Rate Zone 2. Do not go over zone 2! Cool down with 1 mile easy running. Record the Total Time for three miles as well as mile splits. If done on the treadmill, get total time and average speed, if possible. Run on a 1% incline for MAF Test if done on the treadmill.

Title: Run, Tempo (2 x 1 mile tempo + 2 x 800 tempo)

Run half a mile easier in between, letting your heartrate come down. Then run 2 x 800 at best effort Take 2 minutes recovery between these two. I prefer this on a track but on the road is okay too. Go into whatever zone you can on these. Cool down with any remaining time in Z1/low Z2. Log your 2 mile repeat times, and your 2 800 times.

Title: Supplemental Strength C (2 rounds)
WorkoutDescription: Do two sets of 15 repetitions of each exercise, using approximately 60 percent of your one-repetition maximum resistance. Rest 30 to 60 seconds between sets. Title: Swim, Z3 Descending Builds {5000}
WorkoutDescription: Warm up 400 swim w/fins 300 kick w/fins 200 pull 4 x 100 des 1-4 @ 1:25 Main Set (3600m) 2 x 400 build x 100 @ 5:30 1 x 800 pace (85%) w/fins @30 sec rest 2 x 300 build x 100 @ 4:15 1 x 600 pace (85%) w/fins + paddles @30 sec 2 x 200 build x 50 @ 2:45 1 x 400 pace (85%) no fins 100 cool down easy

Title: Z2 Aerobic Bike with Big Gear efforts, 3 x 10
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Ride in Zone 2 today, pushing to the upper half of Zone 2 if feeling good. A little riding in low zone 3 during the big gear efforts is okay, but don't force it. Include 3 x 10 minutes at "big gear" efforts in high z2. Shift into a gear that puts your cadence approximately at 65-75 rpm. Focus on smooth, steady pedal strokes. Ride 5 minutes high cadence in between efforts in Z2 Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: Z3 Run, Tempo Intervals: 6 x 800m Repeats
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Do 4 X 50 meters of drills (butt-kicks, side shuffle, high knees, skipping, etc.) plus 4 X 50 meter striders. Run 6 X 800 meters (2 laps) in low to MID Zone 3. Recovery is 400 m jog. No walking recovery in this tempo workout! Run any remaining time easy to cool down.

Title: Z3 Swim, Neg Splits/50s {4200}
WorkoutDescription: ‎500 Swim 200 Kick 300 Pull 4x100 des 1-4 @ 1:30/1:40/1:45 Main 1 x 400 neg split @ 6:00/6:40/7:00 4 x 50 swim @ 50 1 x 300 neg split @ 4:30/5:00/5:20 4 x 50 swim @ 50 1 x 200 neg split @ 3:00/3:20/3:30 4 x 50 swim @ 50 1 x 100 neg split @ 1:30/1:40/1:45 4 x 50 swim @ 50 Swim 200 back/breaststroke Pull 2 x 300 with buoy. 200 easy

Title: Z2 Long Endurance Bike with Z3/Z4 Tempo Intervals 4 x 30
WorkoutDescription: Warmup up 30 minutes Easy. Ride 1 hour in upper zone 1 to lower zone 2, by power and heartrate. Ride 4 X 30 minutes of Z3-low Z4 Intervals. Lower intensity for 15 minutes in between these intervals. Ride any remaining time after the intervals in Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy. Cadence range is 80-105 rpm, with cadence mostly in the 90s. Practice race day nutrition plan.

Title: Z2 Aerobic Run + drills
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy. Run Aerobic Zone 2 today. Include 6 x 50 meters of running drills toward the end of your run, but before the cool-down: 1) Heel Lifts (feet come right under the hips) 2) Grapevines, alternating one foot in front of the other 3) Fast Feet: focus on landing on the balls of your feet in very short and quick steps 4) Slow Skips: drive tall and slow, alternate arms 5) Backwards running (don't trip!) 6) High Knees Cool down 5 minutes easy.

Title: Z3 Half Ironman Specific Swim
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 8 x 50, first 4 easy, last 4 build within each 50 (10 sec RI) Swim 3 x 1000. First one is at half iron pace @85% Each one gets just a little faster. Pace it so that you can pick up the pace on each one, even if it's just by a second or two. 1 minute rest interval. RECORD times in log!!! Cool down 100 easy kick.

Title: 3/20 Anaerobic/Aerobic LT Test
WorkoutDescription: Warmup: 20 minutes easy in Zones 1 and 2. Ride 3 X 1 minute fast pedaling at 100rpm to get things moving. Ride 5 minutes easy. Perform the test on a relatively flat road or on an indoor trainer. Main Set: Ride 3 minutes ALL OUT BEST EFFORT. Ride easy 10 minutes. Rice 20 min Time Trial BEST EFFORT. Make both of these tests as steady as possible. Do not go too hard at the beginning so that you can't hold a steady effort. Ride any remaining time easy. Cool Down 110 minutes. Record your average heartrate and average normalized power (if using a powermeter) for both the 3 minute and 20 minute efforts.

Title: Bike, Z2 MAF Test
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test to test aerobic capacity on the bike. After a 15 minute warmup, ride an approximately 8-10 mile course (flat or rolling hills) that you can repeat in the future. RIDE IN THE TOP FEW BEATS OF ZONE 2, BUT NOT OVER!!! Record average HR, max HR, average speed, total time and exact distance. Also record details of the course used and any other necessary details. Can be done on the Computrainer. Pick a route you can do again in the future. Ride the rest of the ride in Zones 1 and 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy.
AthleteComments: *04/30/2019 Keith Kruelskie: 141 BPM - 253 W. Think I had a bit more in there... would prob say 255-260*

Title: Run, Tempo (3 x tempo miles + 3 x 1 min hard)
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Run 4 x 30 second pickups with 60 seconds easy. stop, stretch and hydrate. Then run 3 x 1 mile in the middle of zone 3 (do not go over zone 3 at all!). Run half a mile easier in between, letting your heartrate come down. These are not threshold repeat miles! These are TEMPO miles not all out. Then run 3 x 1 minute fast. Take 90 seconds easy jog in-between. Cool down with any remaining time in Z1/low Z2.

Title: Z2 Bike, Big Gear 3 x 5, 4 x 1

Rest 30 to 60 seconds between sets. Squat Lat pulldown Leg extension Bench Press Leg curl (hamstrings) Biceps curl Triceps exercise (choice) Seated row Abdominals (curl-up, reverse & oblique curl, crunch) Side/lateral shoulder raise

Title: Z2 Bike, Big Gear 3 x 5, 4 x 1
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy. Ride low end Zone 2, add some pickups in the warmup. Then ride 3 x 5 minutes at "big gear" efforts. Shift into a gear that allows rpm to be ~60-70, and focus on a smooth steady pedal strokes, ride into zone 3 if feeling good. Ride 3 minutes high cadence in between efforts. Then ride 4 x 1 minute big gear climbs in or out of the saddle. Take 1 minute easy spinning between each. Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: Bike Quality, 3-blocks
WorkoutDescription: Warm-up 10 mins easy spinning followed by 3 x 30 secs in an easy gear at high cadence with 30 secs recovery. Then spin 5 mins easy spinning. Main set 3 x 10 min blocks with 5 mins easy spinning after each one: Block 1: Ride 10 minutes alternating 45 secs hard with15 seconds easy. Use a big gear that puts you around 70 rpms on the hard and don't shift during the easy part... just soft pedal in that big gear. HR/power should go up into Z3 (or 85% by feel) Block 2: Ride 10 minutes alternating 20 secs hard with10 seconds easy. Use a big gear that puts you around 70 rpms on the hard and don't shift during the easy part... just soft pedal in that big gear. HR/power should go up into Z3 (or 85% by feel) Block 3: Ride 10 minutes alternating 20 secs hard out of the saddle and 40 seconds easy in the saddle (shift to easier gear on the 40 easy). Progress across the 10 minutes to make them harder effort as you go. Cool-down any remaining time.

Title: Bike, Speed Drills 8 x 2

Heartrate can go into zone 3 some, but this is more of a fast cadence drill than it is a hard interval workout. Pedal as fast as you can without bouncing. Shift gears so effort is not hard. Ride the remainder of the ride in Zone 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Ride 5 minutes high cadence between each. 10 minutes high after the set Then ride 6 x 1 minute out-of the-saddle big gear climbs in Z2/Z3. Take 2 minutes easy spinning between these. Ride any remaining time in Z2 Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: 100 Mile IRONMAN Prep Ride
WorkoutDescription: Ride the first 25 miles at an easy pace in Z1 to low Z2 (below IM effort). This should feel controlled.Focus on nutrition. Ride the second 25 focused on your bike position. Ride at your target IM race effort (high z2). Stay strictly in aero. Include as much climbing as possible here. Keep your upper body still. Concentrate on efficient, smooth, strong riding. Ride the third 25 miles below your target IM race effort in mid Z2. This should be a marginal drop in effort and not a significant reduction from applying yourself to gentle spinning. Keep the momentum of the ride going. Focus on nutrition and form. Include constant rolling hills/big gears. Ride the final lap at an effort level that’s greater than your IM bike target effort in low Z3.

Title: 3/20 Anaerobic/Aerobic LT Test
WorkoutDescription: Warmup: 20 minutes easy in Zones 1 and 2. Ride 3 X 1 minute fast pedaling at 100rpm to get things moving. Ride 5 minutes easy. Perform the test on a relatively flat road or on an indoor trainer. Main Set: Ride 3 minutes ALL OUT BEST EFFORT. Ride easy 10 minutes. Rice 20 min Time Trial BEST EFFORT. Make both of these tests as steady as possible. Do not go too hard at the beginning so that you can't hold a steady effort. Ride any remaining time easy. Cool Down 110 minutes. Record your average heartrate and average normalized power (if using a powermeter) for both the 3 minute and 20 minute efforts.

Title: Bike, Z2 MAF Test 20 minutes

After a 15 minute warmup, ride an approximately 20 minute course (flat or rolling hills) that you can repeat in the future. RIDE IN THE TOP FEW BEATS OF ZONE 2, BUT NOT OVER!!! Record average HR, average power, average speed, total time and exact distance. Also record details of the course used and any other necessary details. Can be done on a trainer to but pick a file that is mostly flat or slightly uphill. . Ride the rest of the ride in Zones 1 and 2. Cool down 10 minutes easy.

Title: 100 Mile IRONMAN Prep Ride INCLUDING "Climbs"
WorkoutDescription: This 100 mile ride should be done on 4 x 25-mile loops/trainer segments. Ride the first 25 at an easy pace in Z1 to low Z2 (below IM effort). This should feel controlled. If you’re puffing, you’re going too hard! Focus on nutrition. Ride the second 25 focused on your bike position. Ride at your target IM race effort. Stay strictly in aero. Throw in some climbs! Keep your upper body still. Concentrate on efficient, smooth, strong riding. Ride the third 25 miles below your target IM race effort in mid Z2. This should be a marginal drop in effort and not a significant reduction from applying yourself to gentle spinning. Keep the momentum of the ride going. Focus on nutrition and form. Ride the final lap at an effort level that’s greater than your IM bike target effort in low Z3.

Title: Durability Overload Run/Walk Pattern (2:45 run, 60 min walk total 3:45 on your feet)
WorkoutDescription: Run 60 minutes continuous in Z2. Then alternate running 15 minutes in Z2 and speed-walking 30 seconds until for 7 cycles. Run is in Z2. Make much of this on rolling hills, if possible. Walk any remaining time to total 3:30 continuous walk/run. DO NOT RUN MORE THAN 2:45!!!

Title: Run, MAF Test
WorkoutDescription: Maximum Aerobic Function (MAF) Test: how fast you run without going anaerobic at all. This test can be done on the track or the treadmill. (Track is preferable). Warmup with 2 miles easy running. TEST: Run 3 miles continuous in the last few beats of your Aerobic Heart Rate Zone 2. Do not go over zone 2! Cool down with 1 mile easy running. Record the Total Time for three miles as well as mile splits. If done on the treadmill, get total time and average speed, if possible. Run on a 1% incline for MAF Test if done on the treadmill.

Title: Run, Treadmill "Uncles" by speed
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10-15 minutes easy. Do 4 sets of these following "uncles": Start the treadmill at 5% grade and set the speed so you are in high zone 2. Every 20 seconds, increase the speed by .3 mph. Quit increasing the speed when you cannot keep your form (obviously stop before you get sloppy and fall off!!). Heartrate may go very high. Allow 3-4 minutes in-between each set. Run any remaining time in low zone 2. Cool down 5 minutes easy jogging. Good luck!!

WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Run 4 x 30 second pickups with 60 seconds easy. stop, stretch and hydrate. Then run 2 x 1 mile in the middle of zone 3 (do not go over zone 3 at all!). Take 90 seconds easy jog in-between. Cool down with any remaining time in Z1/low Z2.

Title: Z2 Bike, Big Gear 4 x 5, 5 x 1
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy. Ride low end Zone 2, add some pickups in the warmup. Then ride 4 x 5 minutes at "big gear" efforts. Shift into a gear that allows rpm to be ~60-70, and focus on a smooth steady pedal strokes, ride into zone 3 if feeling good. Ride 3 minutes high cadence in between efforts. Then ride 5 x 1 minute big gear climbs in or out of the saddle. Take 1 minute easy spinning between each. Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: Bike, Power Intervals (Steady Effort) 2 X [3X3]
WorkoutDescription: Power Intervals, Steady Effort Warmup 15 minutes easy spinning Ride 3 x 1 minute high cadence drills to get body going. Main Set: 2 sets of 3 X 3 minutes Power Intervals (VERY HARD, above lactate threshold in Zones 5 and 6). Rest 3 minutes in between intervals and 6 minutes in between sets. Cool down 10-15 minutes easy. On an RPE scale of 1-10, Power Intervals should feel like a 10. Heartrate is at maximum. Steady Effort means that power output and work effort are steady across the interval.

Title: Run, Tempo Fartlek: Step-Down Ladder 2
WorkoutDescription: Tempo Fartlek (alternating speeds) Run. Warmup 10 minutes easy. Run 20 minutes Z2 Run the following Fartlek Ladder Run 3 x 4 minutes TEMPO in zone 3. Run 3 x 2 minutes HARD at 90%/5K effort Run 3 x 1 minute VERY HARD. Run 3 x 30 second BEST EFFORT... very fast running with good form. Jog 90 seconds easy recovery in-between each of these. Run any remaining time/mileage in zone 1/2. Cool down 5 minutes easy.

Title: Restorative: Stretch and Foam Roll
WorkoutDescription: Stretch: 10 min light stretching focusing on all major muscle groups. Hold each stretch 60 secons. Foam Roll the Quads, Glutes, Calves, and IT bands. Roll the feet/arches on a ball (like a tennis ball) Spend a couple minutes on each area with extra time on tight/painful.

Title: ~Shake out run
WorkoutDescription: Easy peazy. Stop if anything hurts. Don't worry about heartrate. Just go by feel and loosen the legs up.

Title: Z2 Long Aerobic Run
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy. Run aerobic effort in Aerobic EnduranceZone 2. Progress the run from the bottom of zone 2 to the top throughout the run. Cool down 5 minutes easy. Cadence is 90+ steps per minute. Record average HR below.

Title: Strength, core/upper body
WorkoutDescription: Perform 20 minutes of core work, including abdominal and back exercises. Also include some arm exercises like pushups, bicep curls, tricep extensions, lat pulldowns, and shoulder raises. Some core examples can be found here: https://www.self.com/gallery/21-incredibly-effective-abs-exercises-you-can-do-instead-of-crunches

Title: Long Z2 Bike with 2 x 10 min BSE + 4 X 5 Big Gear
WorkoutDescription: Warmup: 30 minutes Easy/Endurance pace. 3 X 1 minute fast pedaling at 100rpm (1 min RI) 5 minutes Easy Riding Main Set: 20 min best all -out effort Make this effort as steady as possible. Do not go too hard the first 5 minutes. This is done ALL OUT as if it were a race. Ride 4 x 5 minutes big gear effort as these. Z2 unless easily going into Z3. Take 5 minutes easy spinning between these. Ride any remaining time in Z1/Z2 as you feel. In the post-activity comments, for your 2 x 10 min efforts, please log: 1) average Heartrate 2) average non-norm power (if using a powermeter) 3) cadence 4) speed (if done on an out and back course or smart trainer.

Title: The MACH 5 MONDAY "CHECK-IN"
WorkoutDescription: The 5 in "MACH 5" refers to the five fundamental areas in life that affect athletic performance including training, health/rest, nutrition, balance, and mental/emotional. Please give me some details about the following 5 areas for today/last week: . 1) Training: how do you feel in general about your recent training and motivation? . 2) Health/Restoration: How many hours of sleep have you been getting the last few nights and how is the quality of your sleep? Are you stretching? Do you have any sniffles/sore throat/cough/abnormal fatigue, etc? Do you have any problem areas, muscularly or otherwise? . 3) Nutrition, how has your nutrition been the last few days? What was your morning weight? . 4) Life/Balance: How has your life-balance of work/school/family/play/stress/etc been this last week? . 5) Mental/Emotional: how ya feeling in general? Anything affecting your training or racing that I should be aware of?

Title: Simple Core Routine
WorkoutDescription: Do 2 rounds of Crunches, bicycles, plank, superman. Rotate through these until you get to at least 10 minutes, max 15. Some examples can be found here: https://www.self.com/gallery/21-incredibly-effective-abs-exercises-you-can-do-instead-of-crunches

Title: Z2 Aerobic Hilly Run
WorkoutDescription: Warmup easy. Run mostly in zone 2 today but run a hilly route, and allow heartrate to go into LOW zone 3 on the uphills. But don't force heartrate up. Can be done on a treadmill with about 15 minutes total running at 5% grade. Cool down 5 minutes easy jogging.

Title: Z2 Bike, Big Gear 3 x 5, 4 x 1
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy. Ride low end Zone 2, add some pickups in the warmup. Then ride 3 x 5 minutes at "big gear" efforts. Shift into a gear that allows rpm to be ~60-70, and focus on a smooth steady pedal strokes, ride into zone 3 if feeling good. Ride 3 minutes high cadence in between efforts. Then ride 4 x 1 minute big gear climbs in or out of the saddle. Take 1 minute easy spinning between each. Cool down 10 min with high cadence zone 1 riding.

Title: Hip Stretching Routine
WorkoutDescription: Following these 8 exercises stretching the hips and core. Do not rush this. https://gmb.io/hip-mobility/ 1. Lying Hip Rotations 2. Piriformis Stretch 3. Butterfly 4. Frog 5. Kneeling Lunge 6. Traveling Butterfly 7. Squatting Internal Rotations 8. Pigeon

Title: Swim, Z4 Fast 500s {4000}
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 500 Freestyle. Kick 100 Pull 100 Drill 2 x 100 Distance per stroke Swim 8 X 50, descending to race effort. 10-15 sec RI MAIN SET: 4 X 500 with no more than 60 seconds rest. If anything, descend them a little. Done at least at 90% effort. Swim 100 Breaststroke easy. Swim 100 Backstroke easy. Swim 6 X 50 drill with perfect bilateral breathing. Cool down 200 choice

Title: Run, Z3/Z4 Tempo 8 x 2 minutes tempo
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 10 minutes easy running. Run 20 minutes in Z2 Then run 8 x 2 minutes at low Z3/Z4 or 90% by feel. Run 2 minutes easy in between each. Cool down easy to round out the total time.

Title: Bike, TT Tempo Intervals: 2 X 15 (sub LT)
WorkoutDescription: Tempo (sub Lactate Threshold) intervals Warmup 15 minutes ineasy. Ride 10-20 minutes in Aerobic Zone 2, then do 4 X 30 second pickups with 1 minute recovery between each. Ride a few minutes easy, stop and stretch if feeling tight. Bike 2 X 15 minutes (or 10K if you prefer distance) building from low to high zone 3. Avoid Zone 4. Ride 5 minutes recovery between intervals. High Tempo Zone 3 should feel like an 8.5 out of 10 on the Perceived Exertion scale, Zone 4 should feel like a 9 out of 10. Cool down 10 minutes in Active Recovery.

Title: Long Bike with Power Intervals 2 X [3X3]
WorkoutDescription: Power Intervals, Steady Effort Warmup 15 minutes easy. Keep the first half of the ride in low zone 2. In the second half of the ride, include 2 sets of 3 X 3 minutes Power Intervals (AS HARD AS YOU CAN GO keeping the effort steady across the 3 minutes and across all the intervals. Take 3-5 minute recoveries. If riding with a group, have some fun and throw these intervals in the mix as an "attack". Cool down 10-15 minutes easy. On an RPE scale of 1-10, Power Intervals should feel like a 10. Heartrate is at maximum. Steady State means that power output and work effort are steady across the interval.

Title: Z3+ Bike with hard pickups 15-30-60 x 4
WorkoutDescription: Warmup 15 minutes easy. Do two sets of the following at the best effort you can hold. Keep in mind that we want to progress the workout (actually all workouts should finish harder than you start). Bike the following set two times: 4 x 15 seconds hard 4 x 30 seconds hard 4 x 60 seconds hard 4 x 30 seconds hard 4 x 15 seconds hard Take 30 seconds rest between everything. Take 5 minutes easy between the two sets. Heartrate/power is in upper zones. Cool down 5 minutes easy
